You are building "TravelPulse India" - a comprehensive travel news aggregation website for Indian travelers. This is a production-ready application that will be deployed to Vercel and used by thousands of travelers and tourism professionals.

## PROJECT OVERVIEW
Build a Next.js 14 website that automatically aggregates travel news from 20+ sources, displays visa information, travel advisories, government initiatives, and daily tourism facts. The website must be mobile-responsive, SEO-optimized, and include dark mode support.

## TECH STACK REQUIREMENTS
- Frontend: Next.js 14 (App Router), React 19, TypeScript, Tailwind CSS 4, shadcn/ui
- Backend: Next.js API Routes, Prisma ORM, PostgreSQL
- News Fetching: RSS Parser (cheerio), Axios
- Scheduling: node-cron
- AI: DeepSeek API for news categorization
- Icons: lucide-react
- Utilities: date-fns, slugify, zod

## DATABASE SCHEMA (Prisma)
Generate models for: Article, VisaUpdate, TravelAdvisory, GovernmentUpdate, DailyFact, and TravelAlert.

Generate the complete, production-ready directory setup for this project inside my opened workspace folder. Write out every single file in full, create all required sub-folders (/app, /components, /lib, /prisma), and initialize the config files. Do not use abbreviations or placeholders.